41     #define GET_SYMBOL_DB(code) \
42         Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings1, this); \
43         const SymbolDatabase *db = getSymbolDB_inner(tokenizer, code, "test.cpp"); \
44         ASSERT(db);
45     
46     #define GET_SYMBOL_DB_C(code) \
47         Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings1, this); \
48         const SymbolDatabase *db = getSymbolDB_inner(tokenizer, code, "test.c");
49     
50     class TestSymbolDatabase: public TestFixture {
51     public:
52         TestSymbolDatabase()
53             :TestFixture("TestSymbolDatabase")
54             ,nullScope(nullptr, nullptr, nullptr)
55             ,vartok(nullptr)
56             ,typetok(nullptr) {
57         }
58     
59     private:
60         const Scope nullScope;
61         const Token* vartok;
62         const Token* typetok;
63         Settings settings1;
64         Settings settings2;
65     
66         void reset() {
67             vartok = nullptr;
68             typetok = nullptr;
69         }
70     
71         const static SymbolDatabase* getSymbolDB_inner(Tokenizer& tokenizer, const char* code, const char* filename) {
72             errout.str("");
73             std::istringstream istr(code);
74             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, filename);
75             return tokenizer.getSymbolDatabase();
76         }
77     
78         static const Scope *findFunctionScopeByToken(const SymbolDatabase * db, const Token *tok) {
79             std::list<Scope>::const_iterator scope;
80     
81             for (scope = db->scopeList.begin(); scope != db->scopeList.end(); ++scope) {
82                 if (scope->type == Scope::eFunction) {
83                     if (scope->classDef == tok)
84                         return &(*scope);
85                 }
86             }
87             return nullptr;
88         }
89     
90         static const Function *findFunctionByName(const char str[], const Scope* startScope) {
91             const Scope* currScope = startScope;
92             while (currScope && currScope->isExecutable()) {
93                 if (currScope->functionOf)
94                     currScope = currScope->functionOf;
95                 else
96                     currScope = currScope->nestedIn;
97             }
98             while (currScope) {
99                 for (const Function & i : currScope->functionList) {
100                     if (i.tokenDef->str() == str)
101                         return &i;
102                 }
103                 currScope = currScope->nestedIn;
104             }
105             return nullptr;
106         }

405         void array() {
406             GET_SYMBOL_DB_C("int a[10+2];");
407             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
408             if (!db)
409                 return;
410             ASSERT(db->variableList().size() == 2); // the first one is not used
411             const Variable * v = db->getVariableFromVarId(1);
412             ASSERT(v != nullptr);
413             if (!v)
414                 return;
415             ASSERT(v->isArray());
416             ASSERT_EQUALS(1U, v->dimensions().size());
417             ASSERT_EQUALS(12U, v->dimension(0));
418         }
419     
420         void stlarray() {
421             GET_SYMBOL_DB("std::array<int, (16 + 4)> arr;");
422             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
423             if (!db)
424                 return;
425             ASSERT(db->variableList().size() == 2); // the first one is not used
426             const Variable * v = db->getVariableFromVarId(1);
427             ASSERT(v != nullptr);
428             if (!v)
429                 return;
430             ASSERT(v->isArray());
431             ASSERT_EQUALS(1U, v->dimensions().size());
432             ASSERT_EQUALS(20U, v->dimension(0));
433         }
434     
435         void test_isVariableDeclarationCanHandleNull() {
436             reset();
437             const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(nullptr, vartok, typetok);
438             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, result);
439             ASSERT(nullptr == vartok);
440             ASSERT(nullptr == typetok);
441             Variable v(nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
442         }
443     
444         void test_isVariableDeclarationIdentifiesSimpleDeclaration() {
445             reset();
446             givenACodeSampleToTokenize simpleDeclaration("int x;");
447             const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(simpleDeclaration.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
448             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result);
449             ASSERT_EQUALS("x", vartok->str());
450             ASSERT_EQUALS("int", typetok->str());
451             Variable v(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
452             ASSERT(false == v.isArray());
453             ASSERT(false == v.isPointer());
454             ASSERT(false == v.isReference());
455         }
456     
457         void test_isVariableDeclarationIdentifiesInitialization() {
458             reset();
459             givenACodeSampleToTokenize simpleDeclaration("int x (1);");
460             const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(simpleDeclaration.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
461             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result);
462             ASSERT_EQUALS("x", vartok->str());
463             ASSERT_EQUALS("int", typetok->str());
464             Variable v(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
465             ASSERT(false == v.isArray());
466             ASSERT(false == v.isPointer());
467             ASSERT(false == v.isReference());
468         }

491             ASSERT(false == v.isArray());

493             ASSERT(false == v.isReference());

522         void test_isVariableDeclarationIdentifiesManyScopes() {
523             reset();
524             givenACodeSampleToTokenize manyScopes("AA::BB::CC::DD::EE x;");
525             const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(manyScopes.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
526             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result);
527             ASSERT_EQUALS("x", vartok->str());
528             ASSERT_EQUALS("EE", typetok->str());
529             Variable v(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
530             ASSERT(false == v.isArray());
531             ASSERT(false == v.isPointer());
532             ASSERT(false == v.isReference());
533         }
534     
535         void test_isVariableDeclarationIdentifiesPointers() {
536             reset();
537             givenACodeSampleToTokenize pointer("int* p;");
538             const bool result1 = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(pointer.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
539             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result1);
540             ASSERT_EQUALS("p", vartok->str());
541             ASSERT_EQUALS("int", typetok->str());
542             Variable v1(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
543             ASSERT(false == v1.isArray());
544             ASSERT(true == v1.isPointer());
545             ASSERT(false == v1.isReference());
546     
547             reset();
548             givenACodeSampleToTokenize constpointer("const int* p;");
549             Variable v2(constpointer.tokens()->tokAt(3), constpointer.tokens()->next(), constpointer.tokens()->tokAt(2), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
550             ASSERT(false == v2.isArray());
551             ASSERT(true == v2.isPointer());
552             ASSERT(false == v2.isConst());
553             ASSERT(false == v2.isReference());
554     
555             reset();
556             givenACodeSampleToTokenize pointerconst("int* const p;");
557             const bool result2 = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(pointerconst.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
558             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result2);
559             ASSERT_EQUALS("p", vartok->str());
560             ASSERT_EQUALS("int", typetok->str());
561             Variable v3(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
562             ASSERT(false == v3.isArray());
563             ASSERT(true == v3.isPointer());
564             ASSERT(true == v3.isConst());
565             ASSERT(false == v3.isReference());
566         }
567     
568         void test_isVariableDeclarationDoesNotIdentifyConstness() {
569             reset();
570             givenACodeSampleToTokenize constness("const int* cp;");
571             const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(constness.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
572             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, result);
573             ASSERT(nullptr == vartok);
574             ASSERT(nullptr == typetok);
575         }

754             const bool result1 = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(var1.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
755             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result1);
756             Variable v1(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
757             ASSERT(false == v1.isArray());
758             ASSERT(false == v1.isPointer());
759             ASSERT(true == v1.isReference());
760     
761             reset();
762             givenACodeSampleToTokenize var2("foo*& bar;");
763             const bool result2 = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(var2.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
764             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result2);
765             Variable v2(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
766             ASSERT(false == v2.isArray());
767             ASSERT(true == v2.isPointer());
768             ASSERT(true == v2.isReference());
769     
770             reset();
771             givenACodeSampleToTokenize var3("std::vector<int>& foo;");
772             const bool result3 = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(var3.tokens(), vartok, typetok);
773             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result3);
774             Variable v3(vartok, typetok, vartok->previous(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
775             ASSERT(false == v3.isArray());
776             ASSERT(false == v3.isPointer());
777             ASSERT(true == v3.isReference());
778         }

824                             "}");

885         void findVariableType1() {
886             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class A {\n"
887                           "public:\n"
888                           "    struct B {};\n"
889                           "    void f();\n"
890                           "};\n"
891                           "\n"
892                           "void f()\n"
893                           "{\n"
894                           "    struct A::B b;\n"
895                           "    b.x = 1;\n"
896                           "}");
897             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
898             if (!db)
899                 return;
900             const Variable* bvar = db->getVariableFromVarId(1);
901             ASSERT_EQUALS("b", bvar->name());
902             ASSERT(bvar->type() != nullptr);
903         }

906             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class A {\n"
907                           "public:\n"
908                           "    class B {\n"
909                           "    public:\n"
910                           "        struct C {\n"
911                           "            int x;\n"
912                           "            int y;\n"
913                           "        };\n"
914                           "    };\n"
915                           "\n"
916                           "    void f();\n"
917                           "};\n"
918                           "\n"
919                           "void A::f()\n"
920                           "{\n"
921                           "    struct B::C c;\n"
922                           "    c.x = 1;\n"
923                           "}");
924             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
925             if (!db)
926                 return;
927             const Variable* cvar = db->getVariableFromVarId(3);

929             ASSERT(cvar->type() != nullptr);

932         void findVariableType3() {
933             GET_SYMBOL_DB("namespace {\n"
934                           "    struct A {\n"
935                           "        int x;\n"
936                           "        int y;\n"
937                           "    };\n"
938                           "}\n"
939                           "\n"
940                           "void f()\n"
941                           "{\n"
942                           "    struct A a;\n"
943                           "    a.x = 1;\n"
944                           "}");
945             (void)db;
946             const Variable* avar = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "a")->variable();
947             ASSERT(avar);
948             ASSERT(avar && avar->type() != nullptr);
949         }

951         void rangeBasedFor() {
952             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void reset() {\n"
953                           "    for(auto& e : array)\n"
954                           "        foo(e);\n"
955                           "}");
956     
957             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
958             if (!db)
959                 return;
960             ASSERT(db->scopeList.back().type == Scope::eFor);
961             ASSERT_EQUALS(2, db->variableList().size());
962             if (db->variableList().size() < 2)
963                 return;
964             const Variable* e = db->getVariableFromVarId(1);
965             ASSERT(e && e->isReference() && e->isLocal());
966         }
967         void isVariableStlType() {
968             {
969                 reset();
970                 std::istringstream code("std::string s;");
971                 TokenList list(nullptr);
972                 list.createTokens(code, "test.cpp");
973                 const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(list.front(), vartok, typetok);
974                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result);
975                 Variable v(vartok, list.front(), list.back(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
976                 static const std::set<std::string> types = { "string", "wstring" };
977                 static const std::set<std::string> no_types = { "set" };
978                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, v.isStlType());
979                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, v.isStlType(types));
980                 ASSERT_EQUALS(false, v.isStlType(no_types));
981                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, v.isStlStringType());
982             }
983             {
984                 reset();
985                 std::istringstream code("std::vector<int> v;");
986                 TokenList list(nullptr);
987                 list.createTokens(code, "test.cpp");
988                 list.front()->tokAt(3)->link(list.front()->tokAt(5));
989                 const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(list.front(), vartok, typetok);
990                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result);
991                 Variable v(vartok, list.front(), list.back(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
992                 static const std::set<std::string> types = { "bitset", "set", "vector", "wstring" };
993                 static const std::set<std::string> no_types = { "bitset", "map", "set" };
994                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, v.isStlType());
995                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, v.isStlType(types));
996                 ASSERT_EQUALS(false, v.isStlType(no_types));
997                 ASSERT_EQUALS(false, v.isStlStringType());
998             }
999             {
1000                 reset();
1001                 std::istringstream code("SomeClass s;");
1002                 TokenList list(nullptr);
1003                 list.createTokens(code, "test.cpp");
1004                 const bool result = nullScope.isVariableDeclaration(list.front(), vartok, typetok);
1005                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, result);
1006                 Variable v(vartok, list.front(), list.back(), 0, AccessControl::Public, nullptr, nullptr, &settings1);
1007                 static const std::set<std::string> types = { "bitset", "set", "vector" };
1008                 ASSERT_EQUALS(false, v.isStlType());
1009                 ASSERT_EQUALS(false, v.isStlType(types));
1010                 ASSERT_EQUALS(false, v.isStlStringType());
1011             }
1012         }

1058         void arrayMemberVar1() {
1059             GET_SYMBOL_DB("struct Foo {\n"
1060                           "    int x;\n"
1061                           "};\n"
1062                           "void f() {\n"
1063                           "    struct Foo foo[10];\n"
1064                           "    foo[1].x = 123;\n"  // <- x should get a variable() pointer
1065                           "}");
1066     
1067             const Token *tok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), ". x");
1068             tok = tok ? tok->next() : nullptr;
1069             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
1070             ASSERT(tok && tok->variable() && Token::simpleMatch(tok->variable()->typeStartToken(), "int x ;"));
1071             ASSERT(tok && tok->varId() == 3U); // It's possible to set a varId
1072         }

1080                           "    foo[1][2].x = 123;\n"  // <- x should get a variable() pointer
1081                           "}");

1118             GET_SYMBOL_DB("int x;\n"
1119                           "int y;\n");
1120     
1121             const Variable* v = db->getVariableFromVarId(2);
1122             // three elements: varId 0 also counts via a fake-entry

1124     
1125             ASSERT_THROW(db->getVariableFromVarId(3), std::out_of_range);
1126         }

1128         void hasRegularFunction() {
1129             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void func() { }\n")
1130     
1131             // 2 scopes: Global and Function
1132             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 2);
1133     
1134             if (db) {
1135                 const Scope *scope = findFunctionScopeByToken(db, tokenizer.tokens()->next());
1136     
1137                 ASSERT(scope && scope->className == "func");
1138                 if (!scope)
1139                     return;
1140                 ASSERT(scope->functionOf == nullptr);
1141     
1142                 const Function *function = findFunctionByName("func", &db->scopeList.front());
1143     
1144                 ASSERT(function && function->token->str() == "func");
1145                 ASSERT(function && function->token == tokenizer.tokens()->next());
1146                 ASSERT(function && function->hasBody());
1147                 ASSERT(function && function->functionScope == scope && scope->function == function && function->nestedIn != scope);
1148                 ASSERT(function && function->retDef == tokenizer.tokens());
1149             }
1150         }

1176         void hasInlineClassFunction() {
1177             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Fred { void func() { } };\n")
1178     
1179             // 3 scopes: Global, Class, and Function
1180             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 3);
1181     
1182             if (db) {
1183                 const Token * const functionToken = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "func");
1184     
1185                 const Scope *scope = findFunctionScopeByToken(db, functionToken);
1186     
1187                 ASSERT(scope && scope->className == "func");
1188                 if (!scope)
1189                     return;
1190                 ASSERT(scope->functionOf && scope->functionOf == db->findScopeByName("Fred"));
1191     
1192                 const Function *function = findFunctionByName("func", &db->scopeList.back());
1193     
1194                 ASSERT(function && function->token->str() == "func");
1195                 ASSERT(function && function->token == functionToken);
1196                 ASSERT(function && function->hasBody() && function->isInline());
1197                 ASSERT(function && function->functionScope == scope && scope->function == function && function->nestedIn == db->findScopeByName("Fred"));
1198                 ASSERT(function && function->retDef == functionToken->previous());
1199     
1200                 ASSERT(db && db->findScopeByName("Fred") && db->findScopeByName("Fred")->definedType->getFunction("func") == function);
1201             }
1202         }

1437         void complexFunctionArrayPtr() {
1438             GET_SYMBOL_DB("int(*p1)[10]; \n"                            // pointer to array 10 of int
1439                           "void(*p2)(char); \n"                         // pointer to function (char) returning void
1440                           "int(*(*p3)(char))[10];\n"                    // pointer to function (char) returning pointer to array 10 of int
1441                           "float(*(*p4)(char))(long); \n"               // pointer to function (char) returning pointer to function (long) returning float
1442                           "short(*(*(*p5) (char))(long))(double);\n"    // pointer to function (char) returning pointer to function (long) returning pointer to function (double) returning short
1443                           "int(*a1[10])(void); \n"                      // array 10 of pointer to function (void) returning int
1444                           "float(*(*a2[10])(char))(long);\n"            // array 10 of pointer to func (char) returning pointer to func (long) returning float
1445                           "short(*(*(*a3[10])(char))(long))(double);\n" // array 10 of pointer to function (char) returning pointer to function (long) returning pointer to function (double) returning short
1446                           "::boost::rational(&r_)[9];\n"                // reference to array of ::boost::rational
1447                           "::boost::rational<T>(&r_)[9];");             // reference to array of ::boost::rational<T> (template!)
1448     
1449             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
1450     
1451             if (db) {
1452                 ASSERT_EQUALS(10, db->variableList().size() - 1);
1453                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(1) && db->getVariableFromVarId(1)->dimensions().size() == 1);
1454                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(2) != nullptr);
1455                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(3) && db->getVariableFromVarId(3)->dimensions().size() == 0);
1456                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(4) != nullptr);
1457                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(5) != nullptr);
1458                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(6) && db->getVariableFromVarId(6)->dimensions().size() == 1);
1459                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(7) && db->getVariableFromVarId(7)->dimensions().size() == 1);
1460                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(8) && db->getVariableFromVarId(8)->dimensions().size() == 1);
1461                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(9) && db->getVariableFromVarId(9)->dimensions().size() == 1);
1462                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(10) && db->getVariableFromVarId(10)->dimensions().size() == 1);
1463                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1464             }
1465         }

1467         void pointerToMemberFunction() {
1468             GET_SYMBOL_DB("bool (A::*pFun)();"); // Pointer to member function of A, returning bool and taking no parameters
1469     
1470             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
1471     
1472             if (db) {
1473                 ASSERT_EQUALS(1, db->variableList().size() - 1);
1474                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->getVariableFromVarId(1) != nullptr);
1475                 if (db->getVariableFromVarId(1))
1476                     ASSERT_EQUALS("pFun", db->getVariableFromVarId(1)->name());
1477                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1478             }
1479         }
1480     
1481         void hasSubClassConstructor() {
1482             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { class Sub; }; class Foo::Sub { Sub() {} };");
1483             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
1484     
1485             if (db) {
1486                 bool seen_something = false;
1487                 for (const Scope & scope : db->scopeList) {
1488                     for (std::list<Function>::const_iterator func = scope.functionList.begin(); func != scope.functionList.end(); ++func) {
1489                         ASSERT_EQUALS("Sub", func->token->str());
1490                         ASSERT_EQUALS(true, func->hasBody());
1491                         ASSERT_EQUALS(Function::eConstructor, func->type);
1492                         seen_something = true;
1493                     }
1494                 }
1495                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, seen_something);
1496             }
1497         }

1499         void testConstructors() {
1500             {
1501                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(); };");
1502                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1503                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eConstructor);
1504                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1505             }
1506             {
1507                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(Foo f); };");
1508                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1509                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eConstructor && !ctor->isExplicit());
1510                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1511             }
1512             {
1513                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { explicit Foo(Foo f); };");
1514                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(4)->function();
1515                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eConstructor && ctor->isExplicit());
1516                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1517             }
1518             {
1519                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(Bar& f); };");
1520                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1521                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eConstructor);
1522                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1523             }
1524             {
1525                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(Foo& f); };");
1526                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1527                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eCopyConstructor);
1528                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1529             }
1530             {
1531                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(const Foo &f); };");
1532                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1533                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eCopyConstructor);
1534                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1535             }
1536             {
1537                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("template <T> class Foo { Foo(Foo<T>& f); };");
1538                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(7)->function();
1539                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eCopyConstructor);
1540                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1541             }
1542             {
1543                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(Foo& f, int default = 0); };");
1544                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1545                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eCopyConstructor);
1546                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1547             }
1548             {
1549                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(Foo& f, char noDefault); };");
1550                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1551                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eConstructor);
1552                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1553             }
1554             {
1555                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(Foo&& f); };");
1556                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1557                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eMoveConstructor);
1558                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1559             }
1560             {
1561                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo { Foo(Foo & & f, int default = 1, bool defaultToo = true); };");
1562                 const Function* ctor = tokenizer.tokens()->tokAt(3)->function();
1563                 ASSERT(db && ctor && ctor->type == Function::eMoveConstructor);
1564                 ASSERT(ctor && ctor->retDef == nullptr);
1565             }
1566         }

1568         void functionDeclarationTemplate() {
1569             GET_SYMBOL_DB("std::map<int, string> foo() {}")
1570     
1571             // 2 scopes: Global and Function
1572             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 2 && findFunctionByName("foo", &db->scopeList.back()));
1573     
1574             if (db) {
1575                 const Scope *scope = &db->scopeList.front();
1576     
1577                 ASSERT(scope && scope->functionList.size() == 1);
1578     
1579                 const Function *foo = &scope->functionList.front();
1580     
1581                 ASSERT(foo && foo->token->str() == "foo");
1582                 ASSERT(foo && foo->hasBody());
1583             }
1584         }

1586         void functionDeclarations() {
1587             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void foo();\nvoid foo();\nint foo(int i);\nvoid foo() {}")
1588     
1589             // 2 scopes: Global and Function
1590             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 2 && findFunctionByName("foo", &db->scopeList.back()));
1591     
1592             if (db) {
1593                 const Scope *scope = &db->scopeList.front();
1594     
1595                 ASSERT(scope && scope->functionList.size() == 2);
1596     
1597                 const Function *foo = &scope->functionList.front();
1598                 const Function *foo_int = &scope->functionList.back();
1599     
1600                 ASSERT(foo && foo->token->str() == "foo");
1601                 ASSERT(foo && foo->hasBody());
1602                 ASSERT(foo && foo->token->strAt(2) == ")");
1603     
1604                 ASSERT(foo_int && !foo_int->token);
1605                 ASSERT(foo_int && foo_int->tokenDef->str() == "foo");
1606                 ASSERT(foo_int && !foo_int->hasBody());
1607                 ASSERT(foo_int && foo_int->tokenDef->strAt(2) == "int");
1608     
1609                 ASSERT(&foo_int->argumentList.front() == db->getVariableFromVarId(1));
1610             }
1611         }

1647                           "}");
1648     
1649             ASSERT(db && errout.str().empty());
1650     
1651             if (db) {
1652                 const Scope *scope = db->findScopeByName("getFormula1");
1653                 ASSERT(scope != nullptr);
1654                 ASSERT(scope && scope->nestedIn == &db->scopeList.front());
1655     
1656                 scope = db->findScopeByName("getServiceImplName");
1657                 ASSERT(scope != nullptr);
1658                 ASSERT(scope && scope->nestedIn && scope->nestedIn->className == "ScVbaFormatCondition");
1659             }
1660         }

1678         void functionLinkage() {
1679             GET_SYMBOL_DB("static void f1() { }\n"
1680                           "void f2();\n"
1681                           "extern void f3();\n"
1682                           "void f4();\n"
1683                           "extern void f5() { };\n"
1684                           "void f6() { }");
1685     
1686             ASSERT(db && errout.str().empty());
1687     
1688             if (db) {
1689                 const Token *f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "f1");
1690                 ASSERT(f && f->function() && f->function()->isStaticLocal() && f->function()->retDef->str() == "void");
1691     
1692                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "f2");
1693                 ASSERT(f && f->function() && !f->function()->isStaticLocal() && f->function()->retDef->str() == "void");
1694     
1695                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "f3");
1696                 ASSERT(f && f->function() && f->function()->isExtern() && f->function()->retDef->str() == "void");
1697     
1698                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "f4");
1699                 ASSERT(f && f->function() && !f->function()->isExtern() && f->function()->retDef->str() == "void");
1700     
1701                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "f5");
1702                 ASSERT(f && f->function() && f->function()->isExtern() && f->function()->retDef->str() == "void");
1703     
1704                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "f6");
1705                 ASSERT(f && f->function() && !f->function()->isExtern() && f->function()->retDef->str() == "void");
1706             }
1707         }

1709         void classWithFriend() {
1710             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Foo {}; class Bar1 { friend class Foo; }; class Bar2 { friend Foo; };")
1711             // 3 scopes: Global, 3 classes
1712             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 4);
1713             if (db) {
1714                 const Scope* foo = db->findScopeByName("Foo");
1715                 ASSERT(foo != nullptr);
1716                 const Scope* bar1 = db->findScopeByName("Bar1");
1717                 ASSERT(bar1 != nullptr);
1718                 const Scope* bar2 = db->findScopeByName("Bar2");
1719                 ASSERT(bar2 != nullptr);
1720     
1721                 if (foo && bar1 && bar2) {
1722                     ASSERT(bar1->definedType->friendList.size() == 1 && bar1->definedType->friendList.front().nameEnd->str() == "Foo" && bar1->definedType->friendList.front().type == foo->definedType);
1723                     ASSERT(bar2->definedType->friendList.size() == 1 && bar2->definedType->friendList.front().nameEnd->str() == "Foo" && bar2->definedType->friendList.front().type == foo->definedType);
1724                 }
1725             }
1726         }

1728         void parseFunctionCorrect() {
1729             // ticket 3188 - "if" statement parsed as function
1730             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void func(i) int i; { if (i == 1) return; }\n")
1731             ASSERT(db != nullptr);
1732     
1733             // 3 scopes: Global, function, if
1734             ASSERT_EQUALS(3, db->scopeList.size());
1735     
1736             ASSERT(findFunctionByName("func", &db->scopeList.back()) != nullptr);
1737             ASSERT(findFunctionByName("if", &db->scopeList.back()) == nullptr);
1738         }

1742                           "int bar() {}\n"
1743                           "void func() {}")
1744             ASSERT_EQUALS(3, db->findScopeByName("func")->bodyStart->linenr());
1745         }

1756         void hasGlobalVariables1() {
1757             GET_SYMBOL_DB("int i;\n")
1758     
1759             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 1);
1760             if (db && db->scopeList.size() == 1) {
1761                 std::list<Scope>::const_iterator it = db->scopeList.begin();
1762                 ASSERT(it->varlist.size() == 1);
1763                 if (it->varlist.size() == 1) {
1764                     std::list<Variable>::const_iterator var = it->varlist.begin();
1765                     ASSERT(var->name() == "i");
1766                     ASSERT(var->typeStartToken()->str() == "int");
1767                 }
1768             }
1769         }

1801         void checkTypeStartEndToken1() {
1802             GET_SYMBOL_DB("static std::string i;\n"
1803                           "static const std::string j;\n"
1804                           "const std::string* k;\n"
1805                           "const char m[];\n"
1806                           "void f(const char* const l;) {}");
1807     
1808             ASSERT(db && db->variableList().size() == 6 && db->getVariableFromVarId(1) && db->getVariableFromVarId(2) && db->getVariableFromVarId(3) && db->getVariableFromVarId(4) && db->getVariableFromVarId(5));
1809             if (db && db->getVariableFromVarId(1) && db->getVariableFromVarId(2) && db->getVariableFromVarId(3) && db->getVariableFromVarId(4) && db->getVariableFromVarId(5)) {
1810                 ASSERT_EQUALS("std", db->getVariableFromVarId(1)->typeStartToken()->str());
1811                 ASSERT_EQUALS("std", db->getVariableFromVarId(2)->typeStartToken()->str());
1812                 ASSERT_EQUALS("std", db->getVariableFromVarId(3)->typeStartToken()->str());
1813                 ASSERT_EQUALS("char", db->getVariableFromVarId(4)->typeStartToken()->str());
1814                 ASSERT_EQUALS("char", db->getVariableFromVarId(5)->typeStartToken()->str());
1815     
1816                 ASSERT_EQUALS("string", db->getVariableFromVarId(1)->typeEndToken()->str());
1817                 ASSERT_EQUALS("string", db->getVariableFromVarId(2)->typeEndToken()->str());
1818                 ASSERT_EQUALS("*", db->getVariableFromVarId(3)->typeEndToken()->str());
1819                 ASSERT_EQUALS("char", db->getVariableFromVarId(4)->typeEndToken()->str());
1820                 ASSERT_EQUALS("*", db->getVariableFromVarId(5)->typeEndToken()->str());
1821             }
1822         }

1841             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void f(const char) {}");
1842     
1843             ASSERT(db && db->functionScopes.size()==1U);
1844             if (db && db->functionScopes.size()==1U) {
1845                 const Function * const f = db->functionScopes.front()->function;
1846                 ASSERT_EQUALS(1U, f->argCount());
1847                 const Variable * const arg1 = f->getArgumentVar(0);
1848                 ASSERT_EQUALS("char", arg1->typeStartToken()->str());
1849                 ASSERT_EQUALS("char", arg1->typeEndToken()->str());
1850             }

1853         void check(const char code[], bool debug = true, const char filename[] = "test.cpp") {
1854             // Clear the error log
1855             errout.str("");
1856     
1857             // Check..
1858             settings1.debugwarnings = debug;
1859     
1860             // Tokenize..
1861             Tokenizer tokenizer(&settings1, this);
1862             std::istringstream istr(code);
1863             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, filename);
1864     
1865             // force symbol database creation
1866             tokenizer.createSymbolDatabase();
1867     
1868             settings1.debugwarnings = false;
1869         }

1871         void functionArgs1() {
1872             {
1873                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("void f(std::vector<std::string>, const std::vector<int> & v) { }");
1874                 ASSERT_EQUALS(1+1, db->variableList().size());
1875                 const Variable* v = db->getVariableFromVarId(1);
1876                 ASSERT(v && v->isReference() && v->isConst() && v->isArgument());
1877                 const Scope* f = db->findScopeByName("f");
1878                 ASSERT(f && f->type == Scope::eFunction && f->function);
1879                 if (f && f->function)
1880                     ASSERT(f->function->argumentList.size() == 2 && f->function->argumentList.front().index() == 0 && f->function->argumentList.front().name() == "" && f->function->argumentList.back().index() == 1);
1881                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1882             }
1883             {
1884                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("void g(std::map<std::string, std::vector<int> > m) { }");
1885                 ASSERT_EQUALS(1+1, db->variableList().size());
1886                 const Variable* m = db->getVariableFromVarId(1);
1887                 ASSERT(m && !m->isReference() && !m->isConst() && m->isArgument() && m->isClass());
1888                 const Scope* g = db->findScopeByName("g");
1889                 ASSERT(g && g->type == Scope::eFunction && g->function && g->function->argumentList.size() == 1 && g->function->argumentList.front().index() == 0);
1890                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1891             }
1892             {
1893                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("void g(std::map<int, int> m = std::map<int, int>()) { }");
1894                 const Scope* g = db->findScopeByName("g");
1895                 ASSERT(g && g->type == Scope::eFunction && g->function && g->function->argumentList.size() == 1 && g->function->argumentList.front().index() == 0 && g->function->initializedArgCount() == 1);
1896                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1897             }
1898             {
1899                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("void g(int = 0) { }");
1900                 const Scope* g = db->findScopeByName("g");
1901                 ASSERT(g && g->type == Scope::eFunction && g->function && g->function->argumentList.size() == 1 && g->function->argumentList.front().hasDefault());
1902                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1903             }
1904             {
1905                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("void g(int*) { }"); // unnamed pointer argument (#8052)
1906                 const Scope* g = db->findScopeByName("g");
1907                 ASSERT(g && g->type == Scope::eFunction && g->function && g->function->argumentList.size() == 1 && g->function->argumentList.front().nameToken() == nullptr && g->function->argumentList.front().isPointer());
1908                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1909             }
1910             {
1911                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("void g(int* const) { }"); // 'const' is not the name of the variable - #5882
1912                 const Scope* g = db->findScopeByName("g");
1913                 ASSERT(g && g->type == Scope::eFunction && g->function && g->function->argumentList.size() == 1 && g->function->argumentList.front().nameToken() == nullptr);
1914                 ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
1915             }
1916         }

1918         void functionArgs2() {
1919             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void f(int a[][4]) { }");
1920             const Variable *a = db->getVariableFromVarId(1);
1921             ASSERT_EQUALS("a", a->nameToken()->str());
1922             ASSERT_EQUALS(2UL, a->dimensions().size());
1923             ASSERT_EQUALS(0UL, a->dimension(0));
1924             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, a->dimensions()[0].known);
1925             ASSERT_EQUALS(4UL, a->dimension(1));
1926             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, a->dimensions()[1].known);
1927         }

1929         void functionArgs4() {
1930             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void f1(char [10], struct foo [10]);");
1931             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db->scopeList.front().functionList.size() == 1UL);
1932             const Function *func = &db->scopeList.front().functionList.front();
1933             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, func && func->argumentList.size() == 2UL);
1934             if (func && func->argumentList.size() == 2UL) {
1935                 const Variable *first = &func->argumentList.front();
1936                 ASSERT_EQUALS(0UL, first->name().size());
1937                 ASSERT_EQUALS(1UL, first->dimensions().size());
1938                 ASSERT_EQUALS(10UL, first->dimension(0));
1939                 const Variable *second = &func->argumentList.back();
1940                 ASSERT_EQUALS(0UL, second->name().size());
1941                 ASSERT_EQUALS(1UL, second->dimensions().size());
1942                 ASSERT_EQUALS(10UL, second->dimension(0));
1943             }
1944         }

1946         void functionArgs5() { // #7650
1947             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class ABC {};\n"
1948                           "class Y {\n"
1949                           "  enum ABC {A,B,C};\n"
1950                           "  void f(enum ABC abc) {}\n"
1951                           "};");
1952             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db != nullptr);
1953             if (db) {
1954                 const Token *f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "f ( enum");
1955                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, f && f->function());
1956                 if (f && f->function()) {
1957                     const Function *func = f->function();
1958                     ASSERT_EQUALS(true, func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type());
1959                     if (func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type()) {
1960                         const Type * type = func->argumentList.front().type();
1961                         ASSERT_EQUALS(true, type->isEnumType());
1962                     }
1963                 }
1964             }
1965         }

2153                 ASSERT_EQUALS(3, db->scopeList.size());
2154                 if (db->scopeList.size() == 3) {
2155                     std::list<Scope>::const_iterator scope = db->scopeList.begin();
2156                     ++scope;
2157                     ASSERT_EQUALS((unsigned int)Scope::eClass, (unsigned int)scope->type);
2158                     ASSERT_EQUALS(1, scope->functionList.size());
2159                     ASSERT(scope->functionList.begin()->functionScope != nullptr);
2160                     if (scope->functionList.begin()->functionScope) {
2161                         const Scope * functionScope = scope->functionList.begin()->functionScope;
2162                         ++scope;
2163                         ASSERT(functionScope == &*scope);
2164                     }
2165                 }
2166             }
2167         }

2169         void functionArgs12() { // #7661
2170             GET_SYMBOL_DB("struct A {\n"
2171                           "    enum E { };\n"
2172                           "    int a[10];\n"
2173                           "};\n"
2174                           "struct B : public A {\n"
2175                           "    void foo(B::E e) { }\n"
2176                           "};");
2177     
2178             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db != nullptr);
2179             if (db) {
2180                 const Token *f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "foo (");
2181                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, f && f->function());
2182                 if (f && f->function()) {
2183                     const Function *func = f->function();
2184                     ASSERT_EQUALS(true, func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type());
2185                     if (func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type()) {
2186                         const Type * type = func->argumentList.front().type();
2187                         ASSERT_EQUALS(true, type->isEnumType());
2188                     }
2189                 }
2190             }
2191         }

2193         void functionArgs13() { // #7697
2194             GET_SYMBOL_DB("struct A {\n"
2195                           "    enum E { };\n"
2196                           "    struct S { };\n"
2197                           "};\n"
2198                           "struct B : public A {\n"
2199                           "    B(E e);\n"
2200                           "    B(S s);\n"
2201                           "};\n"
2202                           "B::B(A::E e) { }\n"
2203                           "B::B(A::S s) { }");
2204     
2205             ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db != nullptr);
2206             if (db) {
2207                 const Token *f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "B ( A :: E");
2208                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, f && f->function());
2209                 if (f && f->function()) {
2210                     const Function *func = f->function();
2211                     ASSERT_EQUALS(true, func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type());
2212                     if (func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type()) {
2213                         const Type * type = func->argumentList.front().type();
2214                         ASSERT_EQUALS(true, type->isEnumType() && type->name() == "E");
2215                     }
2216                 }
2217                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "B ( A :: S");
2218                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, f && f->function());
2219                 if (f && f->function()) {
2220                     const Function *func = f->function();
2221                     ASSERT_EQUALS(true, func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type());
2222                     if (func->argumentList.size() == 1 && func->argumentList.front().type()) {
2223                         const Type * type = func->argumentList.front().type();
2224                         ASSERT_EQUALS(true, type->isStructType() && type->name() == "S");
2225                     }
2226                 }
2227             }
2228         }

2250         void namespaces1() {
2251             GET_SYMBOL_DB("namespace fred {\n"
2252                           "    namespace barney {\n"
2253                           "        class X { X(int); };\n"
2254                           "    }\n"
2255                           "}\n"
2256                           "namespace barney { X::X(int) { } }");
2257     
2258             // Locate the scope for the class..
2259             const Scope *scope = nullptr;
2260             for (const Scope & it : db->scopeList) {
2261                 if (it.isClassOrStruct()) {
2262                     scope = &it;
2263                     break;
2264                 }
2265             }
2266     
2267             ASSERT(scope != nullptr);
2268             if (!scope)
2269                 return;
2270     
2271             ASSERT_EQUALS("X", scope->className);
2272     
2273             // The class has a constructor but the implementation _is not_ seen
2274             ASSERT_EQUALS(1U, scope->functionList.size());
2275             const Function *function = &(scope->functionList.front());
2276             ASSERT_EQUALS(false, function->hasBody());
2277         }

2571         // ticket 3508 (constructor, destructor)
2572         void symboldatabase24() {
2573             GET_SYMBOL_DB("struct Fred {\n"
2574                           "    ~Fred();\n"
2575                           "    Fred();\n"
2576                           "};\n"
2577                           "Fred::Fred() { }\n"
2578                           "Fred::~Fred() { }");
2579             // Global scope, Fred, Fred::Fred, Fred::~Fred
2580             ASSERT_EQUALS(4U, db->scopeList.size());
2581     
2582             // Find the scope for the Fred struct..
2583             const Scope *fredScope = nullptr;
2584             for (const Scope & scope : db->scopeList) {
2585                 if (scope.isClassOrStruct() && scope.className == "Fred")
2586                     fredScope = &scope;
2587             }
2588             ASSERT(fredScope != nullptr);
2589             if (fredScope == nullptr)
2590                 return;
2591     
2592             // The struct Fred has two functions, a constructor and a destructor
2593             ASSERT_EQUALS(2U, fredScope->functionList.size());
2594     
2595             // Get linenumbers where the bodies for the constructor and destructor are..
2596             unsigned int constructor = 0;
2597             unsigned int destructor = 0;
2598             for (const Function & it : fredScope->functionList) {
2599                 if (it.type == Function::eConstructor)
2600                     constructor = it.token->linenr();  // line number for constructor body
2601                 if (it.type == Function::eDestructor)
2602                     destructor = it.token->linenr();  // line number for destructor body
2603             }
2604     
2605             // The body for the constructor is located at line 5..
2606             ASSERT_EQUALS(5U, constructor);
2607     
2608             // The body for the destructor is located at line 6..
2609             ASSERT_EQUALS(6U, destructor);
2610     
2611         }

2669                           "class Bar { class Sub; };\n"
2670                           "class Bar::Sub {\n"
2671                           "    int b;\n"
2672                           "public:\n"
2673                           "    Sub() { }\n"
2674                           "    Sub(int);\n"
2675                           "};\n"

2685                           "class Foo;\n"
2686                           "class Bar;\n"
2687                           "class Sub;\n");
2688             ASSERT(db && db->typeList.size() == 5);

2690                 return;

2692             const Type* Foo = &(*i++);

2694             const Type* Sub = &(*i++);
2695             const Type* Foo_Sub = &(*i++);
2696             const Type* Bar_Sub = &(*i);
2697             ASSERT(Foo && Foo->classDef && Foo->classScope && Foo->enclosingScope && Foo->name() == "Foo");
2698             ASSERT(Bar && Bar->classDef && Bar->classScope && Bar->enclosingScope && Bar->name() == "Bar");
2699             ASSERT(Sub && Sub->classDef && !Sub->classScope && Sub->enclosingScope && Sub->name() == "Sub");
2700             ASSERT(Foo_Sub && Foo_Sub->classDef && Foo_Sub->classScope && Foo_Sub->enclosingScope == Foo->classScope && Foo_Sub->name() == "Sub");
2701             ASSERT(Bar_Sub && Bar_Sub->classDef && Bar_Sub->classScope && Bar_Sub->enclosingScope == Bar->classScope && Bar_Sub->name() == "Sub");
2702             ASSERT(Foo_Sub && Foo_Sub->classScope && Foo_Sub->classScope->numConstructors == 1 && Foo_Sub->classScope->className == "Sub");
2703             ASSERT(Bar_Sub && Bar_Sub->classScope && Bar_Sub->classScope->numConstructors == 2 && Bar_Sub->classScope->className == "Sub");
2704         }

2747                           "public:\n"
2748                           "    struct Wilma { };\n"
2749                           "    struct Barney {\n"
2750                           "        bool operator == (const struct Barney & b) const { return true; }\n"
2751                           "        bool operator == (const struct Wilma & w) const { return true; }\n"
2752                           "    };\n"
2753                           "    Fred(const struct Barney & b) { barney = b; }\n"
2754                           "private:\n"
2755                           "    struct Barney barney;\n"
2756                           "};\n");
2757             ASSERT(db && db->typeList.size() == 3);
2758             if (!db || db->typeList.size() != 3)
2759                 return;
2760             std::list<Type>::const_iterator i = db->typeList.begin();
2761             const Type* Fred = &(*i++);
2762             const Type* Wilma = &(*i++);
2763             const Type* Barney = &(*i++);
2764             ASSERT(Fred && Fred->classDef && Fred->classScope && Fred->enclosingScope && Fred->name() == "Fred");
2765             ASSERT(Wilma && Wilma->classDef && Wilma->classScope && Wilma->enclosingScope && Wilma->name() == "Wilma");
2766             ASSERT(Barney && Barney->classDef && Barney->classScope && Barney->enclosingScope && Barney->name() == "Barney");
2767             ASSERT(db->variableList().size() == 5);
2768             if (db->variableList().size() != 5)
2769                 return;
2770             ASSERT(db->getVariableFromVarId(1) && db->getVariableFromVarId(1)->type() && db->getVariableFromVarId(1)->type()->name() == "Barney");
2771             ASSERT(db->getVariableFromVarId(2) && db->getVariableFromVarId(2)->type() && db->getVariableFromVarId(2)->type()->name() == "Wilma");
2772             ASSERT(db->getVariableFromVarId(3) && db->getVariableFromVarId(3)->type() && db->getVariableFromVarId(3)->type()->name() == "Barney");
2773         }

4636             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class C {\n"
4637                           "    void f() = 0;\n"
4638                           "    C(B b) = 0;\n"
4639                           "    C(C& c) = default;"
4640                           "    void g();\n"
4641                           "};");
4642             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.back().functionList.size() == 4);
4643             if (db && db->scopeList.back().functionList.size() == 4) {
4644                 std::list<Function>::const_iterator it = db->scopeList.back().functionList.begin();
4645                 ASSERT((it++)->isPure());
4646                 ASSERT((it++)->isPure());
4647                 ASSERT(!(it++)->isPure());
4648                 ASSERT(!(it++)->isPure());

4683     
4684         void findFunction1() {
4685             GET_SYMBOL_DB("int foo(int x);\n" /* 1 */
4686                           "void foo();\n"     /* 2 */
4687                           "void bar() {\n"    /* 3 */
4688                           "    foo();\n"      /* 4 */
4689                           "    foo(1);\n"     /* 5 */
4690                           "}");               /* 6 */
4691             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
4692             if (db) {
4693                 const Scope * bar = db->findScopeByName("bar");
4694                 ASSERT(bar != nullptr);
4695                 if (bar) {
4696                     const unsigned int linenrs[2] = { 2, 1 };
4697                     unsigned int index = 0;
4698                     for (const Token * tok = bar->bodyStart->next(); tok != bar->bodyEnd; tok = tok->next()) {
4699                         if (Token::Match(tok, "%name% (") && !tok->varId() && Token::simpleMatch(tok->linkAt(1), ") ;")) {
4700                             const Function * function = db->findFunction(tok);
4701                             ASSERT(function != nullptr);
4702                             if (function) {
4703                                 std::stringstream expected;
4704                                 expected << "Function call on line " << tok->linenr() << " calls function on line " << linenrs[index] << std::endl;
4705                                 std::stringstream actual;
4706                                 actual << "Function call on line " << tok->linenr() << " calls function on line " << function->tokenDef->linenr() << std::endl;
4707                                 ASSERT_EQUALS(expected.str(), actual.str());
4708                             }
4709                             index++;
4710                         }
4711                     }
4712                 }
4713             }
4714         }

4716         void findFunction2() {
4717             // The function does not match the function call.
4718             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void func(const int x, const Fred &fred);\n"

5603     
5604         void valueTypeMatchParameter() {
5605             ValueType vt_int(ValueType::Sign::SIGNED, ValueType::Type::INT, 0);
5606             ValueType vt_const_int(ValueType::Sign::SIGNED, ValueType::Type::INT, 0, 1);
5607             ASSERT_EQUALS((int)ValueType::MatchResult::SAME, (int)ValueType::matchParameter(&vt_int, &vt_int));
5608             ASSERT_EQUALS((int)ValueType::MatchResult::SAME, (int)ValueType::matchParameter(&vt_const_int, &vt_int));
5609             ASSERT_EQUALS((int)ValueType::MatchResult::SAME, (int)ValueType::matchParameter(&vt_int, &vt_const_int));
5610     
5611             ValueType vt_char_pointer(ValueType::Sign::SIGNED, ValueType::Type::CHAR, 1);
5612             ValueType vt_void_pointer(ValueType::Sign::SIGNED, ValueType::Type::VOID, 1); // compatible
5613             ValueType vt_int_pointer(ValueType::Sign::SIGNED, ValueType::Type::INT, 1); // not compatible
5614             ASSERT_EQUALS((int)ValueType::MatchResult::FALLBACK1, (int)ValueType::matchParameter(&vt_char_pointer, &vt_void_pointer));
5615             ASSERT_EQUALS((int)ValueType::MatchResult::NOMATCH, (int)ValueType::matchParameter(&vt_char_pointer, &vt_int_pointer));
5616     
5617             ValueType vt_char_pointer2(ValueType::Sign::SIGNED, ValueType::Type::CHAR, 2);
5618             ASSERT_EQUALS((int)ValueType::MatchResult::FALLBACK1, (int)ValueType::matchParameter(&vt_char_pointer2, &vt_void_pointer));
5619     
5620             ValueType vt_const_float_pointer(ValueType::Sign::UNKNOWN_SIGN, ValueType::Type::FLOAT, 1, 1);
5621             ValueType vt_long_long(ValueType::Sign::SIGNED, ValueType::Type::LONGLONG, 0, 0);
5622             ASSERT_EQUALS((int)ValueType::MatchResult::NOMATCH, (int)ValueType::matchParameter(&vt_const_float_pointer, &vt_long_long));
5623         }
5624

5626                     ASSERT_EQUALS(true, x != nullptr);                                  \
5627                     if (x) ASSERT_EQUALS(true, x->isNoExcept());

5989         void lambda() {
5990             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void func() {\n"
5991                           "    float y = 0.0f;\n"
5992                           "    auto lambda = [&]()\n"
5993                           "    {\n"
5994                           "        float x = 1.0f;\n"
5995                           "        y += 10.0f - x;\n"
5996                           "    }\n"
5997                           "    lambda();\n"
5998                           "}");
5999     
6000             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 3);
6001             if (db && db->scopeList.size() == 3) {
6002                 std::list<Scope>::const_iterator scope = db->scopeList.begin();
6003                 ASSERT_EQUALS(Scope::eGlobal, scope->type);
6004                 ++scope;
6005                 ASSERT_EQUALS(Scope::eFunction, scope->type);
6006                 ++scope;
6007                 ASSERT_EQUALS(Scope::eLambda, scope->type);
6008             }
6009         }
