6049         // #6298 "stack overflow in Scope::findFunctionInBase (endless recursion)"
6050         void circularDependencies() {
6051             check("template<template<class> class E,class D> class C : E<D> {\n"
6052                   "	public:\n"
6053                   "		int f();\n"
6054                   "};\n"
6055                   "class E : C<D,int> {\n"
6056                   "	public:\n"
6057                   "		int f() { return C< ::D,int>::f(); }\n"
6058                   "};\n"
6059                   "int main() {\n"
6060                   "	E c;\n"
6061                   "	c.f();\n"
6062                   "}");
6063         }
6064     
6065         void executableScopeWithUnknownFunction() {
6066             GET_SYMBOL_DB("class Fred {\n"
6067                           "    void foo(const std::string & a = "");\n"
6068                           "};\n"
6069                           "Fred::foo(const std::string & b) { }\n");
6070     
6071             ASSERT(db && db->scopeList.size() == 3);
6072             if (db && db->scopeList.size() == 3) {
6073                 std::list<Scope>::const_iterator scope = db->scopeList.begin();
6074                 ASSERT_EQUALS(Scope::eGlobal, scope->type);
6075                 ++scope;
6076                 ASSERT_EQUALS(Scope::eClass, scope->type);
6077                 const Scope * class_scope = &*scope;
6078                 ++scope;
6079                 ASSERT(class_scope->functionList.size() == 1);
6080                 if (class_scope->functionList.size() == 1) {
6081                     ASSERT(class_scope->functionList.begin()->hasBody());
6082                     ASSERT(class_scope->functionList.begin()->functionScope == &*scope);
6083                 }
6084             }
6085         }
6086     
6087         std::string typeOf(const char code[], const char pattern[], const char filename[] = "test.cpp", const Settings *settings = nullptr) {
6088             Tokenizer tokenizer(settings ? settings : &settings2, this);
6089             std::istringstream istr(code);
6090             tokenizer.tokenize(istr, filename);
6091             const Token* tok;
6092             for (tok = tokenizer.list.back(); tok; tok = tok->previous())
6093                 if (Token::simpleMatch(tok, pattern))
6094                     break;
6095             return tok->valueType() ? tok->valueType()->str() : std::string();
6096         }
6097     
6098         void valuetype() {
6099             // stringification
6100             ASSERT_EQUALS("", ValueType().str());
6101     
6102             Settings s;
6103             s.int_bit = 16;
6104             s.long_bit = 32;
6105             s.long_long_bit = 64;
6106     
6107             // numbers
6108             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("1;", "1", "test.c", &s));
6109             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("32767;", "32767", "test.c", &s));
6110             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("32768;", "32768", "test.c", &s));
6111             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("32768U;", "32768U", "test.c", &s));
6112             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long long", typeOf("2147483648;", "2147483648", "test.c", &s));
6113             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("1U;", "1U"));
6114             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("1L;", "1L"));
6115             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long", typeOf("1UL;", "1UL"));
6116             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long long", typeOf("1LL;", "1LL"));
6117             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long long", typeOf("1ULL;", "1ULL"));
6118             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long long", typeOf("1LLU;", "1LLU"));
6119             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long long", typeOf("1i64;", "1i64"));
6120             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long long", typeOf("1ui64;", "1ui64"));
6121             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("1u;", "1u"));
6122             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("1l;", "1l"));
6123             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long", typeOf("1ul;", "1ul"));
6124             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long long", typeOf("1ll;", "1ll"));
6125             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long long", typeOf("1ull;", "1ull"));
6126             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long long", typeOf("1llu;", "1llu"));
6127             ASSERT_EQUALS("float", typeOf("1.0F;", "1.0F"));
6128             ASSERT_EQUALS("float", typeOf("1.0f;", "1.0f"));
6129             ASSERT_EQUALS("double", typeOf("1.0;", "1.0"));
6130             ASSERT_EQUALS("double", typeOf("1E3;", "1E3"));
6131             ASSERT_EQUALS("long double", typeOf("1.23L;", "1.23L"));
6132     
6133             // Constant calculations
6134             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("1 + 2;", "+"));
6135             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("1L + 2;", "+"));
6136             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long long", typeOf("1LL + 2;", "+"));
6137             ASSERT_EQUALS("float", typeOf("1.2f + 3;", "+"));
6138             ASSERT_EQUALS("float", typeOf("1 + 2.3f;", "+"));
6139     
6140             // promotions
6141             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("(char)1 +  (char)2;", "+"));
6142             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("(short)1 + (short)2;", "+"));
6143             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("(signed int)1 + (signed char)2;", "+"));
6144             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("(signed int)1 + (unsigned char)2;", "+"));
6145             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("(unsigned int)1 + (signed char)2;", "+"));
6146             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("(unsigned int)1 + (unsigned char)2;", "+"));
6147             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("(unsigned int)1 + (signed int)2;", "+"));
6148             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("(unsigned int)1 + (unsigned int)2;", "+"));
6149             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("(signed long)1 + (unsigned int)2;", "+"));
6150             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long", typeOf("(unsigned long)1 + (signed int)2;", "+"));
6151     
6152             // char *
6153             ASSERT_EQUALS("const char *", typeOf("\"hello\" + 1;", "+"));
6154             ASSERT_EQUALS("const char",  typeOf("\"hello\"[1];", "["));
6155             ASSERT_EQUALS("const char",  typeOf(";*\"hello\";", "*"));
6156             ASSERT_EQUALS("const wchar_t *", typeOf("L\"hello\" + 1;", "+"));
6157     
6158             // Variable calculations
6159             ASSERT_EQUALS("void *", typeOf("void *p; a = p + 1;", "+"));
6160             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = x + 1;", "+"));
6161             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = x | 1;", "|"));
6162             ASSERT_EQUALS("float", typeOf("float x; a = x + 1;", "+"));
6163             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("signed x; a = x + 1;", "x +"));
6164             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("unsigned x; a = x + 1;", "x +"));
6165             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("unsigned int u1, u2; a = u1 + 1;",  "u1 +"));
6166             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("unsigned int u1, u2; a = u1 + 1U;", "u1 +"));
6167             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("unsigned int u1, u2; a = u1 + u2;", "u1 +"));
6168             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("unsigned int u1, u2; a = u1 * 2;",  "u1 *"));
6169             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("unsigned int u1, u2; a = u1 * u2;", "u1 *"));
6170             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("int x; a = &x;", "&"));
6171             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("int x; a = &x;", "&"));
6172             ASSERT_EQUALS("long double", typeOf("long double x; dostuff(x,1);", "x ,"));
6173             ASSERT_EQUALS("long double *", typeOf("long double x; dostuff(&x,1);", "& x ,"));
6174             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("struct X {int i;}; void f(struct X x) { x.i }", "."));
6175             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("int *p; a = p++;", "++"));
6176             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = x++;", "++"));
6177             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("enum AB {A,B}; AB *ab; x=ab+2;", "+"));
6178             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("enum AB {A,B}; enum AB *ab; x=ab+2;", "+"));
6179             ASSERT_EQUALS("AB *", typeOf("struct AB {int a; int b;}; AB ab; x=&ab;", "&"));
6180             ASSERT_EQUALS("AB *", typeOf("struct AB {int a; int b;}; struct AB ab; x=&ab;", "&"));
6181             ASSERT_EQUALS("A::BC *", typeOf("namespace A { struct BC { int b; int c; }; }; struct A::BC abc; x=&abc;", "&"));
6182             ASSERT_EQUALS("A::BC *", typeOf("namespace A { struct BC { int b; int c; }; }; struct A::BC *abc; x=abc+1;", "+"));
6183     
6184             // Unary arithmetic/bit operators
6185             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = -x;", "-"));
6186             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = ~x;", "~"));
6187             ASSERT_EQUALS("double", typeOf("double x; a = -x;", "-"));
6188     
6189             // Ternary operator
6190             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = (b ? x : x);", "?"));
6191             ASSERT_EQUALS("", typeOf("int x; a = (b ? x : y);", "?"));
6192             ASSERT_EQUALS("double", typeOf("int x; double y; a = (b ? x : y);", "?"));
6193             ASSERT_EQUALS("const char *", typeOf("int x; double y; a = (b ? \"a\" : \"b\");", "?"));
6194             ASSERT_EQUALS("", typeOf("int x; double y; a = (b ? \"a\" : std::string(\"b\"));", "?"));
6195             ASSERT_EQUALS("bool", typeOf("int x; a = (b ? false : true);", "?"));
6196     
6197             // Boolean operators/literals
6198             ASSERT_EQUALS("bool", typeOf("a > b;", ">"));
6199             ASSERT_EQUALS("bool", typeOf(";!b;", "!"));
6200             ASSERT_EQUALS("bool", typeOf("c = a && b;", "&&"));
6201             ASSERT_EQUALS("bool", typeOf("a = false;", "false"));
6202             ASSERT_EQUALS("bool", typeOf("a = true;", "true"));
6203     
6204             // shift => result has same type as lhs
6205             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = x << 1U;", "<<"));
6206             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int x; a = x >> 1U;", ">>"));
6207             ASSERT_EQUALS("",           typeOf("a = 12 >> x;", ">>", "test.cpp")); // >> might be overloaded
6208             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("a = 12 >> x;", ">>", "test.c"));
6209             ASSERT_EQUALS("",           typeOf("a = 12 << x;", "<<", "test.cpp")); // << might be overloaded
6210             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("a = 12 << x;", "<<", "test.c"));
6211     
6212             // assignment => result has same type as lhs
6213             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned short", typeOf("unsigned short x; x = 3;", "="));
6214     
6215             // array..
6216             ASSERT_EQUALS("void * *", typeOf("void * x[10]; a = x + 0;", "+"));
6217             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("int x[10]; a = x + 1;", "+"));
6218             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int",  typeOf("int x[10]; a = x[0] + 1;", "+"));
6219             ASSERT_EQUALS("",            typeOf("a = x[\"hello\"];", "[", "test.cpp"));
6220             ASSERT_EQUALS("const char",  typeOf("a = x[\"hello\"];", "[", "test.c"));
6221     
6222             // cast..
6223             ASSERT_EQUALS("void *", typeOf("a = (void *)0;", "("));
6224             ASSERT_EQUALS("char", typeOf("a = (char)32;", "("));
6225             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("a = (long)32;", "("));
6226             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("a = (long int)32;", "("));
6227             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long long", typeOf("a = (long long)32;", "("));
6228             ASSERT_EQUALS("long double", typeOf("a = (long double)32;", "("));
6229             ASSERT_EQUALS("char", typeOf("a = static_cast<char>(32);", "("));
6230             ASSERT_EQUALS("", typeOf("a = (unsigned x)0;", "("));
6231             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("a = unsigned(123);", "("));
6232     
6233             // sizeof..
6234             ASSERT_EQUALS("char", typeOf("sizeof(char);", "char"));
6235     
6236             // const..
6237             ASSERT_EQUALS("const char *", typeOf("a = \"123\";", "\"123\""));
6238             ASSERT_EQUALS("const signed int *", typeOf("const int *a; x = a + 1;", "a +"));
6239             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int * const", typeOf("int * const a; x = a + 1;", "+"));
6240             ASSERT_EQUALS("const signed int *", typeOf("const int a[20]; x = a + 1;", "+"));
6241             ASSERT_EQUALS("const signed int *", typeOf("const int x; a = &x;", "&"));
6242             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int * const a; x = *a;", "*"));
6243             ASSERT_EQUALS("const signed int", typeOf("const int * const a; x = *a;", "*"));
6244     
6245             // function call..
6246             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int a(int); a(5);", "( 5"));
6247             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("auto a(int) -> int; a(5);", "( 5"));
6248             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long", typeOf("sizeof(x);", "("));
6249             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("int (*a)(int); a(5);", "( 5"));
6250     
6251             // struct member..
6252             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("struct AB { int a; int b; } ab; x = ab.a;", "."));
6253             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("struct AB { int a; int b; } *ab; x = ab[1].a;", "."));
6254     
6255             // Overloaded operators
6256             ASSERT_EQUALS("Fred", typeOf("class Fred { Fred& operator<(int); }; void f() { Fred fred; x=fred<123; }", "<"));
6257     
6258             // Static members
6259             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("struct AB { static int a; }; x = AB::a;", "::"));
6260     
6261             // Pointer to unknown type
6262             ASSERT_EQUALS("*", typeOf("Bar* b;", "b"));
6263     
6264             // Enum
6265             ASSERT_EQUALS("char", typeOf("enum E : char { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6266             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed char", typeOf("enum E : signed char { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6267             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned char", typeOf("enum E : unsigned char { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6268             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed short", typeOf("enum E : short { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6269             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned short", typeOf("enum E : unsigned short { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6270             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("enum E : int { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6271             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("enum E : unsigned int { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6272             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long", typeOf("enum E : long { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6273             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long", typeOf("enum E : unsigned long { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6274             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed long long", typeOf("enum E : long long { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6275             ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned long long", typeOf("enum E : unsigned long long { }; void foo() { E e[3]; bar(e[0]); }", "[ 0"));
6276     
6277             // Library types
6278             {
6279                 // PodType
6280                 Settings settingsWin64;
6281                 settingsWin64.platformType = Settings::Win64;
6282                 const Library::PodType u32 = { 4, 'u' };
6283                 const Library::PodType podtype2 = { 0, 'u', Library::PodType::INT };
6284                 settingsWin64.library.mPodTypes["u32"] = u32;
6285                 settingsWin64.library.mPodTypes["xyz::x"] = u32;
6286                 settingsWin64.library.mPodTypes["podtype2"] = podtype2;
6287                 ValueType vt;
6288                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, vt.fromLibraryType("u32", &settingsWin64));
6289                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, vt.fromLibraryType("xyz::x", &settingsWin64));
6290                 ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::Type::INT, vt.type);
6291                 ValueType vt2;
6292                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, vt2.fromLibraryType("podtype2", &settingsWin64));
6293                 ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::Type::INT, vt2.type);
6294                 ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int *", typeOf(";void *data = new u32[10];", "new", "test.cpp", &settingsWin64));
6295                 ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int *", typeOf(";void *data = new xyz::x[10];", "new", "test.cpp", &settingsWin64));
6296                 ASSERT_EQUALS("unsigned int", typeOf("; x = (xyz::x)12;", "(", "test.cpp", &settingsWin64));
6297             }
6298             {
6299                 // PlatformType
6300                 Settings settingsUnix32;
6301                 settingsUnix32.platformType = Settings::Unix32;
6302                 Library::PlatformType s32;
6303                 s32.mType = "int";
6304                 settingsUnix32.library.mPlatforms[settingsUnix32.platformString()].mPlatformTypes["s32"] = s32;
6305                 ValueType vt;
6306                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, vt.fromLibraryType("s32", &settingsUnix32));
6307                 ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::Type::INT, vt.type);
6308             }
6309             {
6310                 // PlatformType - wchar_t
6311                 Settings settingsWin64;
6312                 settingsWin64.platformType = Settings::Win64;
6313                 Library::PlatformType lpctstr;
6314                 lpctstr.mType = "wchar_t";
6315                 settingsWin64.library.mPlatforms[settingsWin64.platformString()].mPlatformTypes["LPCTSTR"] = lpctstr;
6316                 ValueType vt;
6317                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, vt.fromLibraryType("LPCTSTR", &settingsWin64));
6318                 ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::Type::WCHAR_T, vt.type);
6319             }
6320             {
6321                 // Container
6322                 Settings sC;
6323                 Library::Container c;
6324                 c.startPattern = "C";
6325                 c.startPattern2 = "C !!::";
6326                 sC.library.containers["C"] = c;
6327                 ASSERT_EQUALS("container(C) *", typeOf("C*c=new C;","new","test.cpp",&sC));
6328                 ASSERT_EQUALS("container(C) *", typeOf("x=(C*)c;","(","test.cpp",&sC));
6329             }
6330             {
6331                 // Container (vector)
6332                 Settings set;
6333                 Library::Container vector;
6334                 vector.startPattern = "Vector";
6335                 vector.startPattern2 = "Vector !!::";
6336                 vector.type_templateArgNo = 0;
6337                 vector.arrayLike_indexOp = true;
6338                 set.library.containers["Vector"] = vector;
6339                 ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("Vector<int> v; v[0]=3;", "[", "test.cpp", &set));
6340             }

6342             // new
6343             ASSERT_EQUALS("C *", typeOf("class C {}; x = new C();", "new"));
6344     
6345             // auto variables
6346             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("; auto x = 3;", "x"));
6347             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("; auto *p = (int *)0;", "p"));
6348             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("; auto data = new int[100];", "data"));
6349             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int", typeOf("; auto data = new X::Y; int x=1000; x=x/5;", "/")); // #7970
6350             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("; auto data = new (nothrow) int[100];", "data"));
6351             ASSERT_EQUALS("signed int *", typeOf("; auto data = new (std::nothrow) int[100];", "data"));
6352             ASSERT_EQUALS("const signed short", typeOf("short values[10]; void f() { for (const auto *x : values); }", "x"));
6353             ASSERT_EQUALS("const signed int", typeOf("; const auto x = 3;", "x"));
6354     
6355             // Variable declaration
6356             ASSERT_EQUALS("char *", typeOf("; char abc[] = \"abc\";", "["));
6357             ASSERT_EQUALS("", typeOf("; int x[10] = { [3]=1 };", "[ 3 ]"));
6358         }

6360         void variadic1() { // #7453
6361             {
6362                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("CBase* create(const char *c1, ...);\n"
6363                               "int    create(COther& ot, const char *c1, ...);\n"
6364                               "int foo(COther & ot)\n"
6365                               "{\n"
6366                               "   CBase* cp1 = create(\"AAAA\", 44, (char*)0);\n"
6367                               "   CBase* cp2 = create(ot, \"AAAA\", 44, (char*)0);\n"
6368                               "}");
6369     
6370                 const Token *f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "create ( \"AAAA\"");
6371                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db && f && f->function() && f->function()->tokenDef->linenr() == 1);
6372                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "create ( ot");
6373                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db && f && f->function() && f->function()->tokenDef->linenr() == 2);
6374             }
6375             {
6376                 GET_SYMBOL_DB("int    create(COther& ot, const char *c1, ...);\n"
6377                               "CBase* create(const char *c1, ...);\n"
6378                               "int foo(COther & ot)\n"
6379                               "{\n"
6380                               "   CBase* cp1 = create(\"AAAA\", 44, (char*)0);\n"
6381                               "   CBase* cp2 = create(ot, \"AAAA\", 44, (char*)0);\n"
6382                               "}");
6383     
6384                 const Token *f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "create ( \"AAAA\"");
6385                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db && f && f->function() && f->function()->tokenDef->linenr() == 2);
6386                 f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "create ( ot");
6387                 ASSERT_EQUALS(true, db && f && f->function() && f->function()->tokenDef->linenr() == 1);
6388             }
6389         }

6449         void noReturnType() {
6450             GET_SYMBOL_DB_C("func() { }");
6451     
6452             ASSERT(db && db->functionScopes.size() == 1);
6453             if (db && db->functionScopes.size() == 1) {
6454                 ASSERT(db->functionScopes[0]->function != nullptr);
6455                 if (db->functionScopes[0]->function != nullptr) {
6456                     const Token *retDef = db->functionScopes[0]->function->retDef;
6457                     ASSERT_EQUALS("func", retDef ? retDef->str() : "");
6458                 }
6459             }
6460         }

6462         void auto1() {
6463             GET_SYMBOL_DB("; auto x = \"abc\";");
6464             const Token *autotok = tokenizer.tokens()->next();
6465             ASSERT(autotok && autotok->isStandardType());
6466             const Variable *var = db ? db->getVariableFromVarId(1) : nullptr;
6467             ASSERT(var && var->isPointer() && !var->isConst());
6468         }

6470         void auto2() {
6471             GET_SYMBOL_DB("struct S { int i; };\n"
6472                           "int foo() {\n"
6473                           "    auto a = new S;\n"
6474                           "    auto * b = new S;\n"
6475                           "    auto c = new S[10];\n"
6476                           "    auto * d = new S[10];\n"
6477                           "    return a->i + b->i + c[0]->i + d[0]->i;\n"
6478                           "}");
6479             const Token *autotok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "auto");
6480             ASSERT(db && autotok && autotok->valueType() && autotok->valueType()->pointer == 1 && autotok->valueType()->typeScope && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType->name() == "S" && autotok->type() == nullptr);
6481     
6482             autotok = Token::findsimplematch(autotok->next(), "auto");
6483             ASSERT(db && autotok && autotok->valueType() && autotok->valueType()->pointer == 0 && autotok->valueType()->typeScope && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType->name() == "S" && autotok->type() && autotok->type()->name() == "S");
6484     
6485             autotok = Token::findsimplematch(autotok->next(), "auto");
6486             ASSERT(db && autotok && autotok->valueType() && autotok->valueType()->pointer == 1 && autotok->valueType()->typeScope && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType->name() == "S" && autotok->type() == nullptr);
6487     
6488             autotok = Token::findsimplematch(autotok->next(), "auto");
6489             ASSERT(db && autotok && autotok->valueType() && autotok->valueType()->pointer == 0 && autotok->valueType()->typeScope && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType && autotok->valueType()->typeScope->definedType->name() == "S" && autotok->type() && autotok->type()->name() == "S");
6490     
6491             vartok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "a =");
6492             ASSERT(db && vartok && vartok->variable() && vartok->variable()->isPointer() && vartok->variable()->type() && vartok->variable()->type()->name() == "S");
6493     
6494             vartok = Token::findsimplematch(vartok->next(), "b =");
6495             ASSERT(db && vartok && vartok->variable() && vartok->variable()->isPointer() && vartok->variable()->type() && vartok->variable()->type()->name() == "S");

6991         void auto8() {
6992             GET_SYMBOL_DB("std::vector<int> vec;\n"
6993                           "void foo() {\n"
6994                           "    for (auto it = vec.begin(); it != vec.end(); ++it) { }\n"
6995                           "}");
6996             const Token *autotok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "auto it");
6997     
6998             ASSERT(autotok);
6999             ASSERT(autotok->valueType());
7000             ASSERT_EQUALS(0, autotok->valueType()->constness);
7001             ASSERT_EQUALS(0, autotok->valueType()->pointer);
7002             ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::UNKNOWN_SIGN, autotok->valueType()->sign);
7003             ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::ITERATOR, autotok->valueType()->type);
7004     
7005             vartok = Token::findsimplematch(autotok, "it =");
7006             ASSERT(vartok);
7007             ASSERT(vartok->valueType());
7008             ASSERT_EQUALS(0, vartok->valueType()->constness);
7009             ASSERT_EQUALS(0, vartok->valueType()->pointer);
7010             ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::UNKNOWN_SIGN, vartok->valueType()->sign);
7011             ASSERT_EQUALS(ValueType::ITERATOR, vartok->valueType()->type);
7012         }

7053         void auto11() {
7054             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void f() {\n"
7055                           "  const auto v1 = 3;\n"
7056                           "  const auto *v2 = 0;\n"
7057                           "}");
7058     
7059             const Token *v1tok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "v1");
7060             ASSERT(v1tok && v1tok->variable() && v1tok->variable()->isConst());
7061     
7062             const Token *v2tok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "v2");
7063             ASSERT(v2tok && v2tok->variable() && !v2tok->variable()->isConst());
7064         }

7066         void auto12() {
7067             GET_SYMBOL_DB("void f(const std::string &x) {\n"
7068                           "  auto y = x;\n"
7069                           "  if (y.empty()) {}\n"
7070                           "}");
7071     
7072             const Token *tok;
7073     
7074             tok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "y =");
7075             ASSERT(tok && tok->valueType() && tok->valueType()->container);
7076     
7077             tok = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "y .");
7078             ASSERT(tok && tok->valueType() && tok->valueType()->container);
7079         }

7081         void unionWithConstructor() {
7082             GET_SYMBOL_DB("union Fred {\n"
7083                           "    Fred(int x) : i(x) { }\n"
7084                           "    Fred(float x) : f(x) { }\n"
7085                           "    int i;\n"
7086                           "    float f;\n"
7087                           "};");
7088     
7089             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
7090     
7091             const Token *f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "Fred ( int");
7092             ASSERT(f && f->function() && f->function()->tokenDef->linenr() == 2);
7093     
7094             f = Token::findsimplematch(tokenizer.tokens(), "Fred ( float");
7095             ASSERT(f && f->function() && f->function()->tokenDef->linenr() == 3);
7096         }

7098         void incomplete_type() {
7099             GET_SYMBOL_DB("template<class _Ty,\n"
7100                           "  class _Alloc = std::allocator<_Ty>>\n"
7101                           "  class SLSurfaceLayerData\n"
7102                           "  : public _Vector_alloc<_Vec_base_types<_Ty, _Alloc>>\n"
7103                           "{     // varying size array of values\n"
7104                           "\n"
7105                           "  using reverse_iterator = _STD reverse_iterator<iterator>;\n"
7106                           "  using const_reverse_iterator = _STD reverse_iterator<const_iterator>;\n"
7107                           "  const_reverse_iterator crend() const noexcept\n"
7108                           "  {   // return iterator for end of reversed nonmutable sequence\n"
7109                           "    return (rend());\n"
7110                           "  }\n"
7111                           "};");
7112     
7113             ASSERT_EQUALS("", errout.str());
7114         }
